587":287,"588":566,"589":373,"590":277,"591":304,"592":567,"593":493,"594":371,"595":361,"596":599,"597":25,"598":26,"599":559,"600":595,"601":73,"602":38,"603":378,"604":368,"605":348,"606":69,"607":427},"orderedDocs":[[24,"**1 minute before**"],[26,"**10 minutes before**"],[537,"**3 recurring threads** — things that show up across more than one day"],[535,"**300 frames** captured"],[534,"**5 days** captured"],[25,"**5 minutes before** (default)"],[536,"**60 distinct things** seen (people, files, sites, and so on)"],[220,"**A local provider keeps everything on your machine.** Connect Ollama or\nLM Studio and your text is processed locally, with no calls off the Mac."],[513,"**A local provider keeps everything on your machine.** Connect Ollama or\nLM Studio and your text is processed locally."],[493,"**A more responsive Mac while recording.** Day Journal capture pauses for the\nduration of a meeting, so screen capture and live transcription no longer\ncompete for the Neural Engine — and it resumes automatically when the meeting\nends."],[460,"**A new \"You\" tab.** A home for your profile: a short portrait of who you are, the traits\nit has noticed, and a timeline of how your days have felt."],[486,"**A page-peel turn.** Days now turn with a subtle page-peel animation instead\nof a flat slide. Honors Reduce Motion."],[422,"**A self-model that develops over time.** The Reflection's observations now become lasting beliefs. When the same pattern recurs across days, it firms up; when it doesn't, it fades. Recurring patterns promote to stable traits, and those traits shape what the Second Brain notices next — so its understanding deepens, not just accumulates."],[451,"**A sidebar for the book.** An always-available table of contents. It auto-hides to give\nthe page room — hover the left edge to peek it open — or pin it from the toggle in the top-left."],[393,"**A steadier Second Brain.** Beliefs no longer fade away prematurely, so your self-model and persona stay populated; chat citations resolve to the right frames after you reopen a conversation; and the self-model keeps updating even in Low Power Mode."],[478,"**AI answers are now formatted.** Responses from Ask, the Second Brain, and\nmeeting Q\\&A render their Markdown — bold, italic, headings, and bullet lists —\ninstead of showing raw \"\\*\\*\" and \"\\*\" characters."],[31,"**All events** — every timed event on your calendar."],[440,"**Always-on sidebar.** The book's Parts are visible by default on launch; unpin from the masthead toggle if you'd rather have the room."],[417,"**Always-visible, always-refreshable.** The Today's Focus rail is now always on screen — even when empty, it shows what to do to surface tasks. A refresh button lets you regenerate on demand."],[447,"**Answers from real content.** Ask \"why do I keep working with this client?\" and the chat reads\nthe actual text of the relevant moments — emails, docs, messages — and grounds its answer\nin them, with citations you can click to jump straight to the frame."],[175,"**Apple Silicon** (M-series). The on-device speech model runs on the Neural\nEngine, so an Apple Silicon Mac is required."],[573,"**Areas** — clusters Hindsight detected in the graph."],[255,"**Ask** — put a question to an AI provider about the conversation as it\nhappens (see below)."],[23,"**At start time**"],[418,"**Auto-extract after meetings.** When a meeting finishes, its action items are extracted automatically — you don't have to do anything."],[597,"**Automatically check for updates** — on by default. Hindsight checks daily."],[598,"**Automatically download updates** — when on, a found update is fetched in the\nbackground so it is ready to install. This is available only while automatic\nchecks are on."],[110,"**Capture focused text (deep read)** reads the focused window's text through\nAccessibility for richer recall. It's off by default, stays on-device, and\nruns through the same redaction gate as everything else. Turn it on under\n**Settings → Capture** if you want it."],[511,"**Capture, transcription, and storage stay local.** Meetings are transcribed\non your Mac with the on-device speech model (Parakeet, which runs on the Neural\nEngine), and your journal database never leaves it."],[218,"**Capture, transcription, and storage stay local.** Meetings are transcribed\non your Mac, and your journal database never leaves it."],[387,"**Choose your embedding model — and it's used everywhere.** The embedding model you pick for Folder Context RAG now drives *both* indexing and search, so your files and your queries are always embedded with the same model (a mismatch used to silently break semantic search). Point it at a local model in Ollama, LM Studio, or oMLX and nothing leaves your Mac; a cloud embedding model only ever receives your file text if you explicitly choose one and grant consent."],[411,"**Cleaner, more useful todos.** Citation markers and raw URLs/IPs no longer leak into your todo titles, and machine-internal detail text is replaced with human guidance. A tighter, higher-quality list."],[466,"**Clearer meetings.** The section is consistently called \"Meetings\", larger calls\nget more distinct speaker colors, the connect-calendar prompt refreshes after you\ngrant access, and a failed prompt now shows an error instead of doing nothing."],[495,"**Clearer Screen Recording setup.** When Hindsight is opened from outside your\nApplications folder — where macOS runs it from a temporary, locked-down copy —\nsetup now tells you to move Hindsight to Applications and reopen it, which is\nthe only way the Screen Recording permission will stick. Previously it pointed\nyou at the \"+\" button, which can't take effect in that case."],[263,"**Click** the pill to open the panel."],[514,"**Cloud is opt-in.** Sending anything to a cloud provider is off until you\nturn it on, and the same gate applies uniformly to journal text, meeting\ntranscripts, chat, and drafts."],[221,"**Cloud is opt-in.** Sending your journal to a cloud provider is off until you\nexplicitly turn it on, and the same gate applies uniformly to journal text,\nmeeting transcripts, chat, and drafts."],[296,"**Cloud providers are gated by consent.** A cloud provider (Anthropic, OpenAI,\nGoogle Gemini, OpenRouter) is only allowed to receive your data after you turn\non **Allow cloud AI to analyze your journal**, which is **off by default**."],[602,"**Colophon → The Apparatus → Check for Updates…**"],[336,"**Colophon** — any setting, landing on its own row."],[337,"**Commands** — actions you can run, like Turn to today or Begin minutes."],[334,"**Commonplace Book** — beliefs you've kept."],[109,"**Context.** The app and window in front, so activities are easy to make sense\nof later."],[123,"**Cooling threads** — things that went quiet (\"Decide if the roadmap is still\nrelevant\")."],[485,"**Day navigation works again.** The left/right arrow keys (and ⌘\\[ / ⌘]) turn\nbetween days without having to click the page first, and the optional\ntwo-finger swipe (Colophon → \"Turn pages with a two-finger swipe\") is reliable."],[145,"**Days/** — one note per captured day, with the day's narrative, a timeline of\nwhat you worked on, and linked lists of the **People**, **Links**, and **Files**\nseen that day. Your own notes for the day come along too. Each note carries\nfrontmatter (`date`, `captures`, `tags`)."],[397,"**Diagnostic logging.** The embeddings path now logs to Console.app (subsystem `com.iannellomarco.hindsight.core`, category `Embeddings` + `FileIndexer`). You can see exactly what model was requested, whether it succeeded, and when the app fell back to the on-device model — filter Console by the subsystem and send the logs when something's off."],[455,"**Dismiss sticks.** When you dismiss something the Second Brain inferred about you, it\nno longer quietly comes back the next day."],[347,"**Emails**"],[427,"**Every answer is now verified.** The Second Brain's honesty guard — which strips any claim it can't ground in your actual captured data — now runs on every chat answer, not just the relational ones."],[152,"**Export graph (GraphML + Mermaid)** writes your knowledge graph — the people,\nsites, and files that recur together — in two visualization-ready formats:"],[586,"**Export graph** — your knowledge graph as GraphML (for yEd, Gephi, Obsidian)\nand Mermaid (for Markdown)."],[585,"**Export Obsidian vault** — daily notes with backlinked people, sites, and\nfiles."],[142,"**Export Obsidian vault** writes your whole journal as a folder of linked\nMarkdown notes — the kind of vault Obsidian, Logseq, or any plain-Markdown editor\ncan open directly."],[57,"**Export** supports several formats with `--format`: `txt` (default),\n`markdown`, `srt`, `vtt`, and `json`. By default the file is written as\n`<title>.<ext>` in the current directory; use `--output <path>` to choose the\nname, or `--stdout` to print instead of writing a file."],[308,"**External agents (MCP).** Lets an external AI agent query your journal\nlocally. It exposes only the structured, already-redacted recall — people,\nfiles, links, and graph — never screenshots. Exposing raw screen text\n(full-text search) is a separate, extra opt-in, and turning the agent server\noff revokes it."],[415,"**Extract Todos from any meeting.** A new checklist button in the meeting detail reads the transcript and pulls out the action items — things you said you'd do, were asked to do, or agreed to. They land in Today's Focus immediately, each tagged with the meeting it came from."],[472,"**Far better speaker separation.** A one-on-one call is no longer split into a\nhandful of phantom speakers, and genuine group meetings keep everyone — the\nspeaker count is no longer capped, so a large call isn't truncated down to a\nfew voices."],[392,"**Faster, more honest day pages.** Opening a day no longer hitches the interface, screenshots use far less memory, the timeline shows the whole day (not just the first stretch of it), per-app time and on-disk storage are reported accurately, and deleting a day takes a single confirmation."],[402,"**File content never leaves your Mac.** The fallback path that used your chat AI for embeddings is now gated to local providers only — a cloud chat provider will never receive your file text for embedding."],[390,"**File search actually uses your vectors.** Semantic file search now runs whenever you've typed a query (multi-word queries used to silently drop to keyword-only), re-indexes only the files that changed instead of re-embedding the whole folder every time, can be cancelled mid-run, and tells you when a folder has nothing to index."],[349,"**Files**"],[541,"**Files** — file paths and named files (matched against an extension list, so\n`roadmap.swift` is recognized but `v1.2` is not)"],[148,"**Files/** — one note per file, backlinked to the days it appeared."],[498,"**Fixed a launch crash on some Macs.** The bundled Daybook fonts failed to\nload on Macs other than the one the app was built on, which could crash\nHindsight at startup. Fonts now load reliably on every Mac."],[158,"**Graph files** — `~/Library/Application Support/Hindsight/GraphExport/`"],[153,"**graph.graphml** — open it in yEd,\nGephi, or Obsidian's graph plugins for an interactive,\nlaid-out view."],[154,"**graph.mermaid** — a Mermaid `graph TD` diagram you\ncan paste straight into Markdown, Obsidian, or Notion, or render at\nmermaid.live."],[150,"**GRAPH\\_REPORT.md** — a map-of-content for the vault: your most-connected\nnodes, surprising connections, and a few questions worth exploring, all\nresolving to the notes above."],[606,"**Help → Hindsight Help** or **Help → View on GitHub** opens the project on\nGitHub: github.com/iannellomarco/hindsight-next."],[260,"**Hide any speaker** — the **Speakers** tab (⌘4 in the detail view)\nshows each participant's talk share. Click **Hide from transcript** on any\nspeaker to remove their turns. Hidden speakers appear in a **Hidden** section\nwith **Unhide** and **Unhide all** controls."],[259,"**Hide my voice** — a one-click toggle at the top of the transcript removes\nyour turns from the view. Nothing is destroyed; bring them back anytime with\nthe same toggle."],[425,"**Hide your voice from transcripts.** A one-click \"Hide my voice\" toggle on any meeting transcript. Your turns disappear from the view, but nothing is destroyed — bring them back anytime. It survives re-analysis too."],[601,"**Hindsight → Check for Updates…** in the menu bar, or"],[444,"**Honest about what vision sees.** The vision setting and the on-day redaction badge now say plainly: captured text is scrubbed, but visible pixels sent for descriptions are not."],[238,"**Hotkey** — press ⇧⌘M from anywhere. The same shortcut stops the\nrecording when you're done."],[569,"**How your picture has changed** — the arc of how the Second Brain's\nunderstanding of you has shifted over time."],[291,"**Insights, Network, and beliefs.** These are computed deterministically from\nyour own history on-device, so they work with no AI provider connected at all."],[458,"**It knows you.** Tell it your name and role (during setup, or anytime in Settings) and\nit speaks to you personally — greeting you by name and writing your day as someone it\nactually knows."],[448,"**It knows you're not your own coworker.** The Second Brain no longer lists you among the\npeople you work with."],[459,"**It learns you.** From your own days it quietly works out things like your role, the\nway you work, and how you've been feeling — and asks you to confirm the important guesses\nbefore trusting them. Nothing is assumed, and anything that feels off is one tap to dismiss."],[132,"**Journal database** (text, timeline, narratives, notes):\n`~/Library/Application Support/HindsightNext/hindsight.db`"],[435,"**Keyboard tabs in meetings.** Switch a meeting's Transcript / Results / Chat / Speakers with `⌘1`–`⌘4`, matching the rest of the app."],[335,"**Lexicon** — corrective words and snippets."],[348,"**Links**"],[147,"**Links/** — one note per web address you returned to, backlinked to the days\nit appeared."],[408,"**Local AI is now reliable enough to be the primary brain.** Hindsight now asks your local model (Ollama, LM Studio, oMLX) for structured JSON output instead of prompting and hoping — the change that makes a 3–8B local model dependable as your main Second Brain, not a fallback. Cloud stays optional and opt-in."],[432,"**Local AI now grounds on the real thing.** When you use an on-device provider (Ollama, Apple Foundation Models, or LM Studio), Hindsight no longer strips contact details from what the model sees — names, emails, and phone numbers are preserved so your Second Brain and chat answers reference real people and projects instead of `[REDACTED:name]`. Nothing leaves your Mac, so there's no privacy cost. Secrets (cards, keys, tokens) are still scrubbed for every provider."],[295,"**Local providers keep everything on your Mac.** Connect a local model runner\n(Ollama, LM Studio, oMLX, or any OpenAI-compatible endpoint on `localhost`)\nand your text is processed on your machine, with no calls off the Mac."],[174,"**macOS 14.2 or later.**"],[389,"**Meaning-aware file chunking.** With a local model configured, files are split into sections by meaning instead of by paragraph or page, so retrieval lands on coherent passages — and it falls back cleanly to structural chunking otherwise. PDFs and spreadsheets keep their page-accurate citations."],[124,"**Meeting action items** — bullets extracted from your meeting transcripts'\n\"Action Items\" sections."],[433,"**Meeting chat speaks up when it fails.** A question to a meeting that can't reach the AI provider now shows the reason inline, instead of going silent or leaving a placeholder message behind."],[463,"**Meeting status updates instantly.** The menu-bar recording glyph, the permission\nprompt when a recording is blocked, and the \"transcribing…\" indicator now reflect\nwhat's happening the moment it changes."],[289,"**Meeting transcription.** Meetings are transcribed by an on-device speech\nmodel. Audio never leaves your Mac."],[492,"**Meetings wait for the speech model.** If you start recording before the\non-device speech model has finished its one-time setup, Hindsight now shows\n\"Preparing speech model…\" and begins once it's ready, instead of recording a\nmeeting that comes back with an empty transcript."],[239,"**Menu bar** — click the Hindsight status item and choose **Start Recording**."],[244,"**Microphone + System Audio** (default) — records your voice and the call\ntogether."],[333,"**Minutes** — a recorded meeting, by title."],[481,"**More accurate speakers.** Tightened speaker separation so a single remote\nparticipant is no longer occasionally split into two, and a slow\nspeaker-detection step no longer holds up the final transcript."],[571,"**Most connected** — the hubs your work threads through."],[464,"**Much better VoiceOver support.** Buttons and controls across the app — Meetings,\nthe Day Journal, the Second Brain, onboarding, and the Index — now announce\nmeaningful names, and secondary text meets WCAG AA contrast."],[249,"**Mute / Unmute** the microphone (mic + system mode only). Muting also pauses\nlive transcription of your voice."],[475,"**Name a meeting from your calendar.** One click names a meeting after the\ncalendar event it overlaps, so your recordings match your schedule."],[487,"**New app icon.** A Daybook cover with the rubric-red ribbon bookmark."],[470,"**New days appear right away.** After you stop and save a day, it now shows up\non the Days page immediately — previously a freshly finished day could stay\nhidden there until you quit and reopened the app."],[219,"**No AI traffic without a provider you choose.** If you don't connect an AI\nprovider, nothing is sent anywhere — Ask the book and the Second Brain simply\nwait until one is configured."],[512,"**No AI traffic without a provider you choose.** Until you connect an AI\nprovider, nothing is sent anywhere — Ask the book and the Second Brain simply\nwait."],[489,"**No more waiting to record.** Previously, starting a meeting could pause on\n\"Preparing speech model…\" while the on-device model loaded. Now recording\nbegins immediately and captures audio from the first second; the speech model\nloads in the background."],[294,"**No provider, no traffic.** If you haven't configured a provider, features\nthat use AI — Ask the book, Second Brain chat, drafting — simply wait. Nothing\nis sent anywhere."],[501,"**Notarized and stapled.** The app is signed, notarized by Apple, and the\nnotarization ticket is stapled into the build. macOS can verify Hindsight\noffline, so the first launch is clean even without a network connection — no\nspurious \"damaged\" or \"cannot be opened\" warnings."],[253,"**Notes** (default) — type your own notes as the meeting runs. They're saved\ncontinuously. An **Insert** menu adds quick snippets like `/decision`,\n`/action`, and `/question`."],[19,"**Notify before meetings** — a quiet note slips in before each meeting begins.\nNothing records on its own."],[157,"**Obsidian vault** — `~/Library/Application Support/Hindsight/ObsidianVault/`"],[18,"**Off** — Hindsight ignores your calendar. This is the default."],[108,"**On-screen text (OCR).** Each frame is read on-device so its text is\nsearchable and recallable. Recognition runs entirely on your Mac."],[434,"**One Send, everywhere.** The ask boxes in the meeting panel, meeting detail, and journal chats now share the same look and the same Send control — a consistent composer across the whole app."],[122,"**Open loops** — files or topics you touched then dropped (\"Close `plan.md` —\nyou touched it 8 days ago and haven't been back\")."],[250,"**Pause / Resume** — pausing stops capture without leaving a gap; the saved\naudio plays back seamlessly."],[117,"**Pause when idle** stops capturing when you step away. On by default, after\n**2 minutes** idle (you can choose 30 seconds, 1, or 2 minutes)."],[540,"**People** — email addresses, and recurring phone numbers"],[146,"**People/** — one note per person, built from the email addresses in your\nhistory. Addresses are humanized into names (`jane.smith@example.com` becomes\n*Jane Smith*), and OCR variants of the same address collapse into a single\nnote. Each note lists the days that person showed up."],[346,"**Phone numbers**"],[400,"**Pick your embeddings model.** Folder Context RAG now has its own provider config in Settings → Intelligence → File Index, parallel to your chat AI. Point it at Harrier OSS v1 0.6B (or any embedding model) in your Ollama, LM Studio, or oMLX instance — independent of your chat model. A refresh-from-provider list helps you pick. With none set, files use the on-device model."],[461,"**Private by default.** All of this stays on your Mac and works with on-device AI. Sharing\nyour profile with a cloud provider takes a separate, explicit opt-in."],[543,"**Projects and tickets** — issue references like `#318`"],[473,"**Re-analyze a meeting.** A new button on a saved meeting re-runs transcription\nand speaker detection on the original audio — so you can pick up these speaker\nimprovements on meetings recorded earlier, without recording again."],[467,"**Rebindable meeting hotkey.** The global start/stop shortcut (default ⌘⇧M) can now\nbe changed in Settings → The Minutes."],[237,"**Record tile** — open the **Meetings** page (or the daybook's Today page)\nand click **Record** on the \"Record a meeting\" tile."],[439,"**Recoverable deletions.** Deleting a day now removes it from the book but offers an *Undo* right after, from Today — so a mistake never costs you a captured day."],[118,"**Reduce work on battery** lightens capture and analysis on battery power."],[566,"**Reflection** (when an AI provider is connected) — the lead card, with two or\nthree genuine observations grounded in your recent captured moments."],[476,"**Refreshed meeting tabs.** The Transcript / Results / Chat / Speakers tabs now\nuse the same thumb-tab style as the rest of the app."],[198,"**Relaunch Hindsight.** macOS only applies this permission when the app\nstarts, so the status may keep reading *Not granted* until you quit and\nreopen. Setup will prompt you to relaunch if it notices the grant hasn't\ntaken effect yet."],[391,"**Reminders that behave.** \"Add to Reminders\" confirms when it worked, won't pile up duplicates, and writes the whole list in one pass — and an imminent meeting's reminder is no longer dropped when notification permission was still warming up."],[474,"**Rename a meeting.** A pencil next to the title renames a meeting at any time."],[270,"**Rename** it from the title."],[403,"**Retrieval uses the right model.** A matching fix ensures the query vectors and the indexed vectors come from the same model, so semantic search actually works (it was silently mismatched before)."],[441,"**Richer timeline.** Every activity row now shows a thumbnail you can click to open full-size — not just the starred moments."],[264,"**Right-click** for **Stop**, **Pause / Resume**, **Open**, and **Cancel**.\nCancel discards the recording and deletes its audio, so it asks you to confirm\nfirst."],[273,"**Save Audio** to export the recording."],[401,"**Saves take effect immediately.** Configuring the embeddings model used to require an app relaunch (a stale-capture bug froze the old config). Now the index and retrieval read the live setting on every call — change the model, hit re-index, and it's used right away."],[288,"**Screen capture and OCR.** The Day Journal periodically captures your screen\nand reads it with on-device OCR. Screenshots are processed and stored locally\nand never uploaded."],[131,"**Screenshots:** `~/Library/Application Support/HindsightNext/journal`"],[107,"**Screenshots.** A frame of your front window, taken on-device at your chosen\ncadence. The default is **every 2 minutes** (you can pick 30 seconds, 1, 2, 5,\nor 10 minutes)."],[443,"**Secret-bearing frames never leave your Mac.** If a screenshot's captured text revealed a card, key, or token, its pixels are no longer sent to a vision provider — the text redactor can't see into the image, so the whole frame is withheld."],[412,"**Send to Reminders, not Notes.** The export now creates one checkable reminder per todo in a \"Hindsight\" list — native checklist, individually completable, syncs to your iPhone. Action items belong in Reminders."],[428,"**Settings you can trust.** Three toggles that promised behavior but never actually did anything have been fixed or removed. The cloud-consent controls are now one clear decision instead of three cross-referencing toggles."],[456,"**Sharper recall.** Asking about a specific person or file now surfaces the right ones\nto jump to, instead of coming up empty on a normally-worded question."],[542,"**Sites** — web addresses, kept specific (`github.com/example/widgets` is its\nown thing, not collapsed into a bare `github.com`)"],[468,"**Smaller fixes.** Onboarding scrolls on small displays, the meeting audio player\nresets at the end of a clip, deleting a custom word asks first, and a failed app\nsummary can be retried."],[388,"**Smarter suggested to-dos.** Today's task suggestions are rephrased into natural, imperative tasks; meeting action items are extracted by the model from the meeting text; and tasks you pull from a specific meeting now stay on the rail when the page refreshes. Each step falls back to the built-in, on-device behavior when no model is connected."],[499,"**Smoother Screen Recording grant.** After you allow Screen Recording, setup\nnow shows a clear **Relaunch Hindsight** step — macOS only applies this\npermission to a freshly launched app, so the relaunch is what makes the grant\ntake effect."],[465,"**Snappier reading.** Opening a finished day, searching the Index, and reading\nstreamed answers are all faster and smoother."],[20,"**Start recording automatically** — Hindsight shows a 5-second cancellable\ncountdown, then begins the minutes."],[502,"**Steadier installs.** Hardened the DMG so dragging Hindsight to Applications\nand opening it the first time just works."],[251,"**Stop** — ends the meeting and starts transcription."],[496,"**Sturdier packaging.** The disk image is now signed unambiguously, and the\ndiagnostics behind the Screen Recording grant were tightened so first-run\nsetup issues are easier to trace."],[572,"**Surprising connections** — strong links between things that aren't both\ncentral, ranked by how many times more often than chance they appear together."],[245,"**System Audio Only** — captures just what's playing on your Mac, with no\nmicrophone. Use this for recordings where your own voice isn't needed."],[396,"**Test Connection for embeddings.** The embeddings provider card now has a \"Test Connection\" button (just like the chat AI). It sends a tiny embed request to your configured endpoint and tells you whether it worked — including the served model and vector dimensions — or shows the exact error. No more guessing whether your model is loaded or the name is right."],[438,"**The Day Index.** Press `⌘L` anywhere to open a chronological overview of every captured day — title, date, and a thumbnail for each, with a density strip showing how much history you've built. Use `↑↓` to move and `Return` to turn straight to a day."],[332,"**The Days** — any page in your Day Journal, by title, summary, or date."],[191,"**The Index** — ⌘K goes anywhere: days, minutes, settings."],[406,"**The page now leads with what the AI actually did.** The Second Brain used to open with templated counting (\"X sits at the center of a lot of what you do\", cycling a few phrases). Now the AI Reflection — grounded observations written from your real captured moments — leads the page, and the templated belief cards are rephrased into varied, specific observations by the model. The vanity stat row is gone. With no AI connected, you get an honest \"connect a model\" prompt instead of fake templated confidence."],[409,"**The Reflection checks itself, and sees the right frames.** Every reflection is now verified against your actual captured data before it sticks — a fabricated name paired with a real citation gets stripped. And it retrieves semantically-relevant frames (not just the most recent ones), so a reflection about \"the migration\" pulls migration moments from across the week."],[421,"**The Reflection.** After you finish a day (or when you open Hindsight in the morning), your Second Brain reads the actual moments it captured — not just the counts, but what was on your screen, in what order, at what time — and writes a short Reflection: two or three genuine observations a thoughtful colleague might make. Every claim points back to the specific moments it noticed it in. It runs on your Mac if you use Apple Foundation Models or Ollama — free, private, no cloud needed."],[192,"**The Ribbon** — the red mark always brings you back to today."],[423,"**The story of becoming.** The \"Who you are\" card on the You tab now tells a narrative — what the Second Brain has come to understand about you, how that's changed recently, and where it sees tension."],[449,"**Tighter privacy at the edge.** When a cloud model is in use, email addresses and phone\nnumbers are scrubbed from what's sent — on top of the existing secret redaction."],[452,"**Timeline previews.** Each moment in a day's timeline now shows a thumbnail you can click\nto open full-size."],[424,"**Today's Focus.** A new panel on Today surfaces suggested to-dos from your patterns — files you opened then dropped, topics that faded, action items from meetings. Check one off, dismiss it, or send the whole list to Apple Notes with one click."],[416,"**Todos from real content, not just patterns.** When an AI provider is connected, Today's Focus now reads the actual text of your meeting transcripts and on-screen captures — not just the statistics — and extracts specific, actionable tasks (\"Send the brief to Jane by Friday\") instead of pattern inferences (\"You haven't touched plan.md in 8 days\")."],[197,"**Toggle Hindsight on.** On recent macOS there's no confirmation dialog —\nflipping the toggle is the grant."],[544,"**Topics** — recurring subjects that tie the above together"],[149,"**Topics/** — \"area\" notes for the clusters Hindsight detected in your graph,\neach linking its members."],[254,"**Transcript** — the live, speaker-labeled transcript. Toggle **Auto-scroll**\nor **Copy** the text so far."],[480,"**Transcription no longer freezes.** A scheduling deadlock could leave the live\ntranscript blank during a meeting and the post-recording \"transcribing…\" step\nstuck indefinitely. Recording and transcription now run on separate lanes — the\nlive transcript fills in during the meeting and the final transcript completes\npromptly."],[190,"**Turn** — the left and right arrows move between days."],[483,"**Visible page controls.** The Days page now has previous / next buttons and a\ndotted day indicator beneath it — one dot per day, with the current day\nhighlighted. Click any dot to jump straight to that day. (The page-turn\ncontrols were previously invisible edge zones.)"],[490,"**Visible transcription progress.** While the model loads, the transcript area\nshows a progress bar instead of a frozen screen, and the transcript fills in as\nsoon as the model is ready. The full meeting is always transcribed when you\nstop."],[30,"**With participants** — any event that has at least one other attendee."],[29,"**With video link** (default) — only events that carry a recognized\nconference link. Hindsight detects Zoom, Google Meet, Microsoft Teams, Webex,\nAround, and Whereby, plus other common meeting URLs."],[568,"**Worth confronting** — a frank, grounded mirror of things your own history\nsuggests, each shown with its evidence. This stays silent unless your tone dial\n(in the Colophon) allows it, and it never fabricates a criticism."],[567,"**Worth noticing** — patterns rising or cooling across your recent days, all\nderived deterministically from your history. Each has a quick action to draft\nan email or a follow-up calendar event from it."],[574,"**Your graph** — an interactive node-and-link canvas you can open with **Show\ngraph**."],[290,"**Your journal and graph.** The journal database, the people, files, sites,\nand beliefs in the Second Brain, and your meeting library are all stored on\nthis Mac."],[407,"**Your Second Brain can now read your files.** Point Hindsight at a workspace folder — a repo, a docs folder, a papers folder — and it indexes everything inside on your Mac: code, markdown, PDFs, images (via OCR), spreadsheets, rich text, email. The Reflection can then connect your screen activity to your own work artifacts, cited by file. \"You switched to Slack right after the compile errors your plan flagged.\" Nothing leaves your Mac; embeddings run on your local model."],[78,"`--base-url` — an absolute `http(s)` URL for self-hosted endpoints."],[79,"`--command` — the subprocess template, required for the `cli` provider."],[66,"`--diarize` — separate speakers and label each turn (Speaker 1, Speaker 2, …).\nTune with `--diar-threshold` (default `0.6`; lower finds more speakers) and\n`--diar-max-speakers` (default `6`)."],[81,"`--dry-run` shows the per-table counts (imported, skipped, unsupported) without\nwriting anything. Add `--json` for a structured report."],[62,"`--engine` — `parakeet` (default), `whisper`, or `app-default` (use whatever\nengine the app is set to)."],[64,"`--format` — `text` (default), `transcript` (timestamped lines), or `json`."],[63,"`--language` — language hint for Whisper, e.g. `en`, `it`."],[77,"`--model` — pick a model. Required for `openaiCompatible`, `lmstudio`, and\n`omlx`; other providers fall back to a conservative default."],[67,"`--no-save` — transcribe without adding the result to your library."],[65,"`--processing` — `raw`, `clean`, or `app-default` (default; follows your\nVocabulary setting). `clean` rebuilds punctuation and applies your custom\nwords."],[85,"`0` — success."],[86,"`1` — a runtime failure (network, provider, transcription, and similar)."],[87,"`2` — user misuse: bad arguments, a missing input file, or a lookup that was\nambiguous or too short."],[563,"> *You're a builder who values deep focus — you work best in long morning blocks,\n> and you've gotten steadier at holding that focus through the afternoon. There's\n> a tension, though: when you hit a compile error, you tend to switch to email —\n> I first noticed this three reflections ago, and it's held.*"],[379,"1.0.0"],[378,"1.0.1"],[369,"1.0.10"],[368,"1.0.11"],[367,"1.0.12"],[377,"1.0.2"],[376,"1.0.3"],[375,"1.0.4"],[374,"1.0.5"],[373,"1.0.6"],[372,"1.0.7"],[371,"1.0.8"],[370,"1.0.9"],[366,"1.1.0"],[365,"1.1.1"],[364,"1.2.0"],[363,"1.3.0"],[362,"1.3.1"],[361,"1.4.0"],[360,"1.4.1"],[359,"1.5.0"],[358,"1.5.1"],[357,"1.5.2"],[356,"1.6.0"],[167,"1\\. Welcome"],[168,"2\\. Set up the Day Journal"],[169,"3\\. Microphone access (optional)"],[170,"4\\. Prepare on-device models"],[171,"5\\. Three moves, one rehearsal"],[172,"6\\. Ready"],[256,"A **checklist button** (✓) in the meeting header reads the transcript and\nextracts action items — things you said you'd do, were asked to do, or agreed\nto. They land in **Today's Focus** immediately, each tagged with the meeting\nthey came from. You'll see them on the Today page."],[105,"A **MOMENTS** count. Press **Mark Moment** to flag something worth\nremembering as it happens; you can add a short note to a moment, too."],[103,"A **RECORDING** indicator with an elapsed clock."],[550,"A belief needs to show up across **at least two days** before it forms."],[453,"A bigger delete control, and clearer labels distinguishing asking the whole book from\nchatting with a single day."],[462,"A broad polish pass: more reliable meeting status, far wider accessibility, and a\nfaster, more consistent interface."],[399,"A dedicated embeddings model picker for Folder Context RAG — and three fixes the adversarial code review caught before they reached you."],[517,"A few gigabytes of free disk space for the speech model, which downloads once\nduring first-time setup."],[176,"A few gigabytes of free disk space for the speech model, which downloads once\nduring setup."],[549,"A few things keep the picture stable and honest:"],[553,"A file or ticket you touched a couple of times and then dropped about a week\nago is flagged as an **open loop**, phrased as a possibility rather than a\nfact."],[469,"A fix so a finished day always shows up where you expect it."],[508,"A floating pill and a live panel with **Notes**, a speaker-labeled\n**Transcript**, and an **Ask** tab."],[477,"A formatting hotfix for AI answers."],[386,"A more AI-driven Second Brain — pick your own embedding model, smarter suggested to-dos, and meaning-aware file indexing — plus a wave of reliability fixes across reminders, your days, and the Second Brain."],[328,"A note on where this runs"],[500,"A packaging release focused on a smoother, more reliable first launch."],[510,"A page that reads across every day you've captured, links the things that keep\nrecurring, and forms plain-language **beliefs** about your focus. It moves\nbetween **Chat**, **Insights**, **Network**, and **Export**. The beliefs,\nInsights, and Network are computed locally and work with no AI provider\nconnected; recall grounds every chat answer in your real history with citations\nback to the moment each claim came from."],[182,"A quick tour of what Hindsight is: a **Day Journal** woven from periodic screen\ncapture, on-device meeting recording, and a design that keeps your data on this\nMac. Press **Get Started**."],[442,"A real privacy hardening for AI vision:"],[309,"A related option, **AI refinement of insights**, is on by default once a\nprovider is configured. It lets the connected AI tidy your beliefs and topics;\nturn it off to keep the plain, deterministic Second Brain. Like everything else,\nit only uses the provider you chose, under the same gate."],[491,"A reliability release for meeting recording — especially your first one after\ninstalling."],[104,"A running **FRAMES** count (screenshots taken so far)."],[505,"A running record of your day, woven from periodic screen capture read with\non-device OCR (Apple Vision). Turn between days with the left and right arrows,\nlet the red Ribbon bring you back to today, and use **Ask the book** on any page\nto pose a question about your day or your history. Screenshots and the journal\ndatabase never leave your Mac."],[269,"A saved meeting keeps its transcript, your notes, and any Ask conversation. You\ncan:"],[552,"A single quiet day can't retire a belief — it fades only after several quiet\ndays in a row."],[494,"A small reliability release for first-run setup."],[431,"A smarter privacy boundary for on-device AI — and a more consistent feel throughout."],[113,"After **Stop & Review**, Hindsight writes up your day and then opens a short\n**review** at the foot of today's page. It's a chat: it shows the running\nsummary, may ask a few follow-up questions to fill in gaps, and lets you add\nnotes. When you're happy, keep the day; or discard it. A kept day is saved as a\nfinished page you can turn back to anytime."],[232,"After a meeting"],[159,"After an export runs, a **Reveal in Finder** button appears next to it — the\nquickest way to jump to the files. The status line below the buttons confirms\nwhat was written (for example, &#x2A;Exported 12 days · 34 people · 18 links · 9\nfiles.* for the vault, or *Exported graph · 60 nodes · 142 edges* for the graph)."],[279,"AI is opt-in"],[312,"All of these settings live in **the Colophon**, Hindsight's settings page. Open\nthe Index with ⌘K and choose **Colophon**, then go to the\n**Intelligence** section."],[445,"And a sweep of reliability and polish: 