card numbers, keys, and one-time codes are never turned into entities. Ubiquitous\nplumbing — sign-in portals, analytics, CDNs, and boilerplate files like\n`README.md` or `package-lock.json` — is filtered out so it never looks like a hub\nof your work."],[297,"Every AI feature passes the same check before anything is sent: if no provider\nis configured the call is declined, a local provider is allowed, and a cloud\nprovider is allowed only with your consent. There is no separate path — journal\ntext, meeting transcripts, chat questions, drafts, and image descriptions all go\nthrough the same gate."],[283,"Every answer is verified"],[311,"Every chat answer from the Second Brain is checked against your actual captured\nhistory before it's shown. If the model invents a person, project, or fact that\nisn't grounded in your data, the claim is stripped out. This verification runs\non every answer — not just the relational ones — so a fabricated claim can never\nslip through regardless of the question type."],[53,"Every command accepts `--json` for clean, machine-readable output. Progress and\nstatus messages go to standard error, so the JSON on standard output stays\npipeable."],[584,"Everything stays on this Mac, and Export only materializes what you've already\ncaptured:"],[130,"Everything stays on this Mac, under your Library:"],[9,"Everything stays on your Mac"],[51,"Exit codes"],[134,"Export"],[529,"Export"],[137,"Export a graph"],[136,"Export an Obsidian vault"],[161,"Export is fully local. It reuses only the redacted, on-device data Hindsight\nhas already captured — secrets such as card numbers, keys, and one-time codes\nare never turned into notes — and nothing is sent anywhere. The files are yours\nto move, edit, and back up however you like."],[160,"Export needs something to materialize, so journal a few days first. If there's\nnothing to write yet, Hindsight tells you so rather than creating an empty vault."],[140,"Export turns what Hindsight has already captured into open, portable files you\ncan browse, link, and visualize in other tools. Nothing new leaves your machine\n— export only writes out the on-device, redacted data you can already see in the\napp. The database stays the source of truth; export is a one-way snapshot you can\nre-run any time."],[228,"Extracting todos from a meeting"],[437,"Find any day in your history at a glance, and never lose one to an accidental delete."],[166,"First-time setup"],[479,"Fixes meeting transcription."],[315,"For a cloud provider, paste your **API key**. For a local provider, leave the\nkey blank."],[579,"For relational or temporal questions (\"how are X and Y connected?\", \"what have\nI been doing around Z?\"), it assembles real evidence from the graph and answers\nfrom that bundle, keeping `[#n]` citations so you can jump to the exact moment\neach claim came from."],[605,"Found a bug, or have an idea? Everything lives in one place:"],[547,"From that graph, Hindsight distills a self-model: a set of one-line **beliefs**\nabout you, each grouped by kind — people you keep dealing with, projects and\nareas of your work, topics that recur, tools and sites you live in, files you\nkeep returning to, rhythms in how you work, and open loops you touched then\ndropped."],[248,"From the header you can:"],[208,"Get started"],[162,"Getting started"],[520,"Getting to know you"],[173,"Granting Screen Recording on recent macOS"],[222,"Head to Getting started to install Hindsight, run\nfirst-time setup, and learn the three moves for turning through your book."],[261,"Hiding persists across re-analysis — if you re-run speaker detection later (to\npick up model improvements), the people you hid stay hidden."],[229,"Hiding speakers"],[32,"Higher-precision filters skip personal blocks and solo focus time. All-day\nevents and meetings you've declined are always skipped, whatever filter you\nchoose."],[116,"Hindsight can also pause on its own:"],[10,"Hindsight can watch your calendar so you never miss