 provider unless you set one up:"],[52,"Hindsight ships with a companion command-line tool, `hindsight-cli`, that talks\nto the same database as the app. Anything you record, transcribe, or learn in\nthe app is visible from the terminal, and anything the CLI writes shows up in\nthe app. It is handy for scripting, exporting, and feeding your transcripts into\nother tools."],[594,"Hindsight updates itself. New versions download and install in the background, so\nyou generally do not need to do anything to stay current."],[43,"hindsight-cli is a companion tool that shares the app's database — list and export meetings, transcribe files on-device, manage speech models, inspect your Second Brain, and run LLM tasks from the terminal."],[589,"How Hindsight keeps itself up to date, how to check manually, and where to report problems."],[277,"How Hindsight keeps your data on-device by default, how optional cloud AI is gated by consent and redacted before it leaves your Mac, and where to configure a provider and keys."],[324,"How the answer is built"],[75,"How the key is resolved, in order: `--api-key` (a literal — discouraged), then\n`--api-key-env` (the name of an environment variable holding the key), then the\nconventional variable for the provider (for example `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`,\n`OPENAI_API_KEY`, `GEMINI_API_KEY`, `OPENROUTER_API_KEY`). Local providers like\n`ollama` need no key."],[524,"How the self-model develops"],[603,"If a newer version exists, Hindsight shows you what changed and offers to install\nit. If you are already current, it tells you so."],[199,"If the Hindsight entry doesn't respond, remove it from the list and re-add\n`/Applications/Hindsight.app&#x60; with the &#x2A;*+** button, then relaunch."],[33,"If you have several calendars, expand **Calendars** to exclude specific ones —\na personal calendar, say, while keeping your work calendar. New calendars are\nincluded by default."],[344,"If you haven't connected a provider, Recall still works. Instead of