s how you ask your book a question and get a real answer back — built\nfrom what you actually saw and recorded, not from the open web. Two surfaces\nwork together: the **Index** for jumping straight to a page, and **Ask the\nBook** for questions that span many days at once."],[353,"Recall reads your own on-device book. Search and the deterministic card results\nstay entirely on your Mac. The streamed prose answer uses whatever AI provider\nyou've connected in the Colophon — and a local provider keeps everything on\nyour Mac for that too."],[224,"Record and transcribe meetings on-device, with a live panel, notes, and an AI Ask tab."],[506,"Record and transcribe meetings on-device. Start one from the Record tile, the\nmenu bar, the Index (**Begin minutes**), or the ⇧⌘M hotkey. Hindsight\ncan watch your calendar and offer to begin a recording when a meeting starts,\nrecognizing Google Meet, Zoom, and Microsoft Teams links."],[507,"Records your **microphone** and your Mac's **system audio** as separate,\ntime-aligned tracks (the default; **System Audio Only** is also available)."],[354,"Release notes"],[580,"Replies are checked against that evidence before they're saved, so a claim the\nhistory doesn't support is stripped out. This verification runs on **every**\nanswer — not just the relational ones — so a fabricated person or project can\nnever slip through."],[164,"Requirements"],[384,"Requirements"],[394,"Requires macOS 14.2 or later, Apple Silicon."],[398,"Requires macOS 14.2 or later, Apple Silicon."],[419,"Requires macOS 14.2 or later, Apple Silicon."],[430,"Requires macOS 14.2 or later, Apple Silicon."],[413,"Requires macOS 14.2 or later, Apple Silicon. Folder Context RAG and the local-AI improvements work best with a local embedding model (we recommend Harrier OSS v1 0.6B, the MLX 8-bit build, in your Ollama or LM Studio instance) — but everything degrades gracefully to the on-device model when none is running."],[404,"Requires macOS 14.2 or later, Apple Silicon. We recommend Harrier OSS v1 0.6B (the MLX 8-bit build) in your Ollama or LM Studio instance for file embeddings."],[271,"Run **prompt templates** against it — Summary, Action Items & Decisions,\nChapter Breakdown, and more."],[233,"Run a summary automatically"],[73,"Run language-model tasks from the terminal. Unlike the app, the CLI is\nconfigured per call — you pass the provider and key on each invocation; nothing\nis stored."],[509,"Saved meetings keep their transcript, notes, and any Ask conversation, and can\nbe renamed and re-run through prompt templates."],[120,"Screenshots are pruned automatically by the **Keep screenshots for** setting —\n**30 days** by default, or 7, 90, or Forever. Lowering it deletes older captures\non its next pass; \"Forever\" never auto-deletes."],[47,"Second Brain"],[206,"Second Brain"],[382,"Second Brain"],[518,"Second Brain"],[13,"Select **Grant Calendar Access**. macOS will ask for permission once."],[17,"Set **Calendar behavior** to one of three modes:"],[304,"Social Security numbers"],[258,"Sometimes you want to share a transcript without your own voice in it — or\nwithout a noisy participant. In any saved meeting:"],[225,"Start a recording"],[90,"Start capturing"],[331,"Start typing and it filters across everything in one place:"],[593,"Support and feedback"],[74,"Supported providers: `anthropic`, `openai`, `openaiCompatible`, `gemini`,\n`openrouter`, `ollama`, `lmstudio`, `omlx`, and `cli` (a local subprocess)."],[350,"Tap one to seed the search and see every matching moment."],[265,"The **Ask** tab lets you query an AI provider about the live transcript and your\nnotes without leaving the call. The empty state offers browsable quick prompts\ngrouped under **Catch Up**, **Capture**, and **Challenge** — for example\n\"Summarize so far\", \"Action items\", and \"What should I ask?\". Pinned follow-ups\nlike \"Tell me more\" and \"Counter-argument?\" sit above the input once a thread\nis going."],[565,"The **Insights** tab surfaces what's worth your attention right now:"],[570,"The **Network** tab is the graph at a glance:"],[562,"The &#x2A;*\"Who you are\"** card on the You tab synthesizes the self-model into a\nnarrative — not a label, but a story of how the Second Brain's understanding of\nyou is developing. It describes what it's come to understand, how that's changed\nrecently, and where it sees tension:"],[84,"The `errorType` field comes from a small, stable vocabulary — for example\n`auth`, `config`, `connection`, `lookup`, `model`, `rate_limit`,\n`input_missing`, `input_empty`, and `validation` — so scripts can branch on the\nkind of failure."],[92,"The AI day narrative"],[345,"The Ask the Book view offers one-tap chips for the things people look for most:"],[7,"The countdown"],[38,"The countdown only appears when you're not already recording, and only for\nmeetings you've accepted or tentatively accepted (and your own untracked\nblocks). Meetings you haven't responded to won't auto-record, since recording an\nunaccepted meeting would be a surprise — but you can still get a reminder for\nthem."],[97,"The Day Index"],[195,"The Day Journal and meeting recording both rely on the **Screen & System Audio\nRecording** permission. On recent macOS, granting it has one quirk worth knowing."],[211,"The Day Journal is today's page in your book — a running record of what you did,\nso you can reflect on your decisions later. Turn between days with the left and\nright arrows, and use **Ask the book** on any page to pose a question about your\nday or your history."],[100,"The Day Journal is today's page in your book. While it runs, Hindsight quietly\ntakes a screenshot of your front window every couple of minutes, reads the text\non screen so you can recall anything you saw, and — when you stop for the day —\nwrites the day up for you to review and keep."],[183,"The Day Journal periodically captures your screen and reads it with on-device\nOCR to weave a private narrative of your day. Screenshots never leave your Mac."],[450,"The Days page is also redesigned:"],[93,"The end-of-day review"],[504,"The first release of Hindsight: a private, on-device daybook for macOS. One\ncontinuous book you turn through page by page, with three pillars and an Index\n(⌘K) that jumps anywhere."],[181,"The first time you open Hindsight, it opens a first-run setup that walks you\nthrough a few short steps. A &#x2A;*Step *n* of *N*** counter sits in the top-right,\nand you can step back at any time with the chevron. Permission steps are\noptional and can be skipped with **Skip — I'll set this up later**; only the\non-device model step has to finish before you continue."],[230,"The floating pill"],[341,"The full Ask the Book view searches **anything you saw, across every day**.\nType a question — \"what was the address jane.smith sent me?\", \"which build\nbroke last Thursday?\" — and the book answers from your own captured history."],[322,"The Index: jump anywhere"],[521,"The knowledge graph"],[227,"The live panel"],[246,"The microphone **Mute** control is available only in Microphone + System Audio\nmode."],[185,"The microphone is **not** required for journaling — you can skip the next step\nand the Day Journal still works."],[186,"The microphone is only used for **meeting** capture. Grant it now if you plan to\nrecord meetings, or skip it and enable it later from the Colophon."],[205,"The Minutes"],[213,"The Minutes records and transcribes your meetings on-device. Start a recording\nfrom the Index or with ⇧⌘M; Hindsight can also watch your calendar\nand offer to begin minutes when a meeting starts, recognizing Google Meet, Zoom,\nand Microsoft Teams links. Finished meetings are saved to your Library with a\ntitle you can rename."],[564,"The narrative is grounded in the accumulated evidence, and it distinguishes\nwhat's firm (stable traits) from what's still emerging (new patterns). It\nupdates as the self-model develops — so it tells a story of becoming, not a\nstatic portrait."],[112,"The narrative is the one part that draws on an AI provider. Connect one under\n**Settings → AI Provider** — a local provider keeps everything on your Mac.\nCapture, text recognition, search, and storage never need a provider."],[72,"The output lists each belief with its salience, confidence, and evidence count,\nand reports how many would be kept versus dropped by the current guard. Add\n`--include-inactive` to also show dormant or retired beliefs."],[252,"The panel has three tabs, switchable with ⌘1–⌘3:"],[70,"The Parakeet engine (`parakeet-tdt-0.6b-v3`) downloads automatically the first\ntime it is used, so `download` is only needed for `whisper`. Use `warm-up` to\nprepare an engine ahead of time (it may download on first run), and `clear` to\nremove cached models from disk."],[523,"The Reflection"],[558,"The Reflection needs an AI provider. The beliefs, Insights cards, and Network\nwork without one. A local provider (Ollama, Apple Foundation Models) keeps the\nReflection on your Mac."],[557,"The Reflection runs on your Mac if you use Apple Foundation Models or Ollama —\nfree, private, no cloud needed. It appears as the lead card in Insights."],[559,"The Reflection's observations don't just appear and vanish — they become lasting\nbeliefs. When the same pattern recurs across days, the observation is reinforced\nand its confidence grows. When it doesn't recur, it fades. Patterns that recur\nenough times promote to stable **traits** — durable dispositions like \"you work\nbest in long morning blocks\" or \"you avoid documentation until pressure builds.\""],[530,"The Second Brain is the Commonplace Book in Hindsight: the page that reflects\nyour own work back to you. It reads across every day you've captured, links the\nthings that keep recurring, and forms a small set of plain-language beliefs about\nwhat you focus on. You can read those beliefs directly, explore how everything\nconnects, and talk through your history."],[215,"The Second Brain learns from what you capture. Chat with your history, browse\nthe Insights it has noticed, explore the Network of how people, projects, and\nideas connect, and Export what you find — including drafting an email or a\ncalendar event from the conversation."],[446,"The Second Brain now answers from what your screens actually showed — not just who and\nwhat kept recurring."],[532,"The Second Brain only starts answering once it has seen enough of your work to be\nuseful rather than confidently wrong. The page shows where it stands — **Still\nlearning you**, **Getting to know you**, or **Ready** — with a progress bar and\nfour counts: days, frames, things, and threads."],[525,"The story of becoming"],[575,"The tab also offers a few starter questions; tapping one drops you into Chat with\nthat question already asked."],[203,"The three pillars"],[210,"The window is page-based. Turn left and right between days, jump anywhere with\nthe Index (⌘K), and let the red Ribbon bring you back to today.\nEverything you capture stays on this Mac."],[236,"There are three ways to begin:"],[582,"There's also an **Explain** field for two specific things — enter a person, file,\nor site on each side and Hindsight shows the shared bridges between them, drawn\nonly from your graph."],[307,"These are all **off by default** and each is independently controlled in the\nColophon:"],[257,"This also happens **automatically** when a meeting finishes — you don't have to\npress the button. But if you edit the transcript, hide a speaker, or just want\nto re-extract, the button is there."],[188,"This download happens once. If a future launch already has the model cached, the\nstep finishes instantly. If setup stalls (for example, on a slow network), use\n**Retry**."],[11,"This is strictly opt-in. Until you connect a calendar and pick a behavior,\nHindsight ignores your calendar entirely."],[561,"This is the closed loop: observe → believe → reinforce or revise → perceive\ndifferently → observe again. The understanding deepens, not just accumulates.\nAnd it's honest at every step: observations are grounded in real captured\nmoments, every chat answer is verified against the evidence, and beliefs that\ndon't hold up decay and retire."],[184,"This step asks for the **Screen & System Audio Recording** permission. Press\n**Enable Day Journal**, then toggle Hindsight on in the System Settings pane\nthat opens. The same grant also covers meeting recording later, so you only\ngrant it once. See Granting Screen Recording\nbelow if the status doesn't update right away."],[560,"Those traits then shape what the Second Brain notices next. Its perception is\nconditioned on what it already understands: if it has learned you're a methodical\ndebugger, it pays attention when you break that pattern — and the breakage is\noften the most interesting signal. A higher-order reflection pass periodically\nreads the accumulated beliefs and synthesizes higher-level themes (\"your\navoidance of docs and tests both point to deferring unglamorous work\") and\ntensions (patterns that pull in different directions)."],[313,"To connect a provider:"],[106,"To wrap up, press **Stop & Review**. **Discard** throws the session away."],[96,"Today's Focus"],[414,"Today's Focus is now smarter, always visible, and reachable from every meeting."],[410,"Today's Focus is sharper and lands in Reminders:"],[127,"Today's Focus refreshes when you open the page and after you finish a day's\nreview."],[45,"Transcribe"],[60,"Transcribe any audio or video file with the on-device speech engines. The file\nis decoded to audio and recognized locally — nothing leaves your Mac."],[426,"Trust and privacy hardening:"],[599,"Turn either off if you would rather decide when to update."],[274,"Turn on **Run marked prompts automatically** under \"After each meeting\" to have\nchosen templates (the **Summary** template is marked by default) run as soon as\na meeting finishes. Because this sends the transcript to your AI provider, it's\noff until you switch it on. Use &#x2A;*Edit Prompts…** to add, pin, hide, or reset\nthe built-in prompts."],[484,"Turning the pages — fixed, and nicer."],[98,"Turning through your days"],[454,"Two fixes to the Second Brain."],[22,"Under **Remind me**, choose how far ahead you're nudged:"],[577,"Under the hood, recall grounds every answer in your real history rather than\ninventing anything:"],[588,"Updates & Support"],[592,"Updates and your meetings"],[59,"Use `-` in place of text to read from standard input."],[129,"Use the left and right arrows to turn between days. The red Ribbon always brings\nyou back to today, and **Turn to today** is also available from the Index\n(⌘K, shortcut T)."],[201,"Welcome"],[355,"What changed in each version of Hindsight, newest first."],[91,"What gets captured"],[144,"What you get:"],[326,"What you keep coming back to"],[385,"What's new in Hindsight, newest first. Hindsight keeps itself up to date, and\nyou can check manually from the Colophon under **The Apparatus → Check for\nupdates**."],[318,"When a cloud provider is selected, the **Allow cloud AI** master toggle appears\nunder **The Second Brain** — one trust decision, with **Share your profile** as\nan optional sub-toggle for sending your name and role. When a local provider is\nselected, the cloud toggles are hidden and you'll see a simple \"Your AI runs on\nyour Mac — nothing leaves this device.\" Under **External Readers** you'll find\nthe agent (MCP) toggles."],[126,"When an AI provider is connected, the to-do titles are optionally rephrased into\nclearer imperative voice (\"Finish and close `plan.md`\") — but the detection\nitself is deterministic and always works, even offline."],[546,"When two things keep appearing together, that co-occurrence becomes a link. The\nresult is a cross-day graph of who and what your work threads through."],[555,"When you connect an AI provider, the Second Brain gains a deeper layer: **the\nReflection**. After you finish a day — or when you open Hindsight in the morning\n— it reads the actual moments it captured (not just the counts, but *what was on\nyour screen, in what order, at what time*) and writes a short Reflection: two or\nthree genuine observations a thoughtful colleague might make."],[21,"When you pick a non-Off mode, Hindsight will ask for notification permission so\nreminders can appear. If notifications are turned off in System Settings,\nHindsight shows a warning with a shortcut to fix it."],[268,"When you press **Stop**, Hindsight transcribes the audio on-device and saves the\nmeeting to your **Recent meetings** list. The pill confirms with a checkmark and\nclears itself shortly after."],[241,"When you start, Hindsight checks for Microphone and Screen Recording access. If\neither is missing, it points you to System Settings. The first time, grant both\nso capture can run."],[310,"When you use a local provider (Ollama, Apple Foundation Models, LM Studio),\nnothing leaves your Mac — so there's no privacy cost to sending the full,\nun-redacted context. Hindsight preserves real names, emails, and phone numbers\nfor local providers so the Second Brain grounds on the real thing instead of\n`[REDACTED:name]` placeholders. Secrets (cards, keys, tokens) are still scrubbed\nfor every provider, local or cloud."],[340,"When you want an answer rather than a destination, ask the book. Open today's\npage and use the &#x2A;*Ask the book…** bar, or press ⇧⌘A from anywhere\nto jump there and start typing."],[138,"Where the files land"],[284,"Where to configure it: the Colophon"],[99,"Where your data is stored"],[285,"Where your keys are stored"],[6,"Which events count"],[262,"While a meeting is active, a small pill floats on top of every app. It pulses\nwith your audio levels while recording, dims with pause bars when paused, shows\na spinner while transcribing, and a checkmark when the meeting is saved."],[102,"While capture is running you'll see:"],[55,"Work with your saved meeting recordings and their transcripts."],[125,"You can **check one off**, **dismiss** it, or **Add to Notes** — which creates a\nchecklist note in Apple Notes with one click. (The first time, macOS asks for\nAutomation permission to control Notes; grant it once and it's automatic\nafterwards.)"],[240,"You can also begin from the Index: ⌘K → **Begin minutes**."],[600,"You can look for a new version at any time:"],[554,"You can read all of this with no AI provider connected — the beliefs are\ncomputed locally and shown as cards."],[56,"You can refer to a meeting by its full ID, a unique ID prefix (at least four\nhex characters), or a unique title."],[200,"You can revisit any of this later. Screen Recording, microphone, and calendar\naccess can all be re-checked and changed from the **Colophon** (open the Index\nwith ⌘K → **Colophon**)."],[596,"You can tune this in the **Colophon** under **The Apparatus** (open the Index\nwith ⌘K → **Colophon**, then go to the Apparatus section):"],[141,"You'll find it in the Second Brain. Open it from the Index (⌘K) and\ngo to the **Export** tab (⌘4)."],[319,"Your API key is stored only in the **macOS Keychain**, in a per-provider entry\nunder a Hindsight-specific service. It is never written to the app's\npreferences and never appears in your saved configuration. Switching providers\nkeeps each provider's key in the Keychain, so you can move back and forth without\nre-entering it. Pressing **Clear** removes the active provider's key from the\nKeychain."],[266,"Your Ask conversation carries over to the saved meeting, so you can keep working\nwith it afterward."],[519,"Your cross-day knowledge graph — the people, projects, and files you keep returning to, the beliefs Hindsight forms about your focus, and how recall draws on them."],[420,"Your Second Brain now genuinely thinks about your work — and the whole app got sharper, more honest, and more consistent."],[405,"Your Second Brain now leads with genuine AI insight, reads your own files, and works reliably on local models — all on-device, all private."],[457,"Your Second Brain now understands *you* — not just the people, files, and projects in\nyour work, but who you are and how your days have been going."]],"type":"string"},"page_id":{"docs":{"1":22,"2":23,"3":24,"4":25,"5":26,"6":27,"7":28,"8":29,"9":30,"10":31,"11":32,"12":33,"13":34,"14":35,"15":36,"16":37,"17":38,"18":39,"19":40,"20":41,"21":42,"22":43,"23":44,"24":45,"25":46,"26":47,"27":48,"28":49,"29":50,"30":51,"31":52,"32":53,"33":54,"34":55,"35":56,"36":57,"37":58,"38":59,"39":60,"40":61,"41":62,"42":63,"43":64,"44":65,"45":66,"46":67,"47":68,"48":69,"49":70,"50":71,"51":72,"52":73,"53":74,"54":75,"55":76,"56":77,"57":78,"58":79,"59":80,"60":81,"61":82,"62":83,"63":84,"64":85,"65":86,"66":87,"67":88,"68":89,"69":90,"70":91,"71":92,"72":93,"73":94,"74":95,"75":96,"76":97,"77":98,"78":99,"79":100,"80":101,"81":102,"82":103,"83":104,"84":105,"85":106,"86":107,"87":108,"88":109,"89":110,"90":111,"91":112,"92":113,"93":114,"94":115,"95":116,"96":117,"97":118,"98":119,"99":120,"100":121,"101":122,"102":123,"103":124,"104":125,"105":126,"106":127,"107":128,"108":129,"109":130,"110":131,"111":132,"112":133,"113":134,"114":135,"115":136,"116":137,"117":138,"118":139,"119":140,"120":141,"121":142,"122":143,"123":144,"124":145,"125":146,"126":147,"127":148,"128":149,"129":150,"130":151,"131":152,"132":153,"133":154,"134":155,"135":156,"136":157,"137":158,"138":159,"139":160,"140":161,"141":162,"142":163,"143":164,"144":165,"145":166,"146":167,"147":168,"148":169,"149":170,"150":171,"151":172,"152":173,"153":174,"154":175,"155":176,"156":177,"157":178,"158":179,"159":180,"160":181,"161":182,"162":183,"163":184,"164":185,"165":186,"166":187,"167":188,"168":189,"169":190,"170":191,"171":192,"172":193,"173":194,"174":195,"175":196,"176":197,"177":198,"178":199,"179":200,"180":201,"181":202,"182":203,"183":204,"184":205,"185":206,"186":207,"187":208,"188":209,"189":210,"190":211,"191":212,"192":213,"193":214,"194":215,"195":216,